1
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:37,600
=Meeting You=

2
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:41,560
=Episode 17=
=I Like Everything You Make=

3
00:01:41,640 --> 00:01:43,640
(College of Architecture)

4
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:47,710
It's been two days
since you students enrolled.

5
00:01:47,790 --> 00:01:51,900
So, you have some basic understanding
of the school.

6
00:01:51,980 --> 00:01:53,900
Some students also reported...

7
00:01:53,980 --> 00:01:58,300
that the ratio of boys to girls
in our class is seriously out of balance.

8
00:01:58,380 --> 00:02:02,210
Yes, it's too serious.

9
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:05,710
This is also an existing problem
in our department.

10
00:02:05,790 --> 00:02:10,190
But there is no problem
that cannot be solved.

11
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:13,740
The 13-character policy...
Just get used to it.

12
00:02:13,820 --> 00:02:18,910
Happiness lies in contentment.
Cherish the person in front of you.

13
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:26,530
One of our classmates
hasn't met everyone yet.

14
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:32,790
I will now officially introduce him
to everyone.

15
00:02:32,870 --> 00:02:35,080
Who is that?

16
00:02:36,810 --> 00:02:39,750
Come and introduce yourself to everyone.

17
00:02:39,830 --> 00:02:40,760
Okay.

18
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:43,540
Gao Ting.

19
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,880
Thank you.

20
00:02:47,120 --> 00:02:50,450
Okay, find a seat to sit down.

21
00:02:50,530 --> 00:02:54,730
This Gao Ting doesn't seem good
to get along with.

22
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,500
I am Gao Ting.

23
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:04,660
Nan Xi.

24
00:03:09,190 --> 00:03:12,030
Okay, let's go back to class.

25
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:15,090
Everybody knows that the name
of our major...

26
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:18,260
is Architectural Design.

27
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:20,880
I believe everyone
is already eager to try...

28
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,000
when applying for our major.

29
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:27,210
Now, congratulations to all of you.

30
00:03:27,290 --> 00:03:31,550
Your dreams have come true.

31
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:35,970
Complete an architectural model design
within two weeks.

32
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:37,150
Two weeks?

33
00:03:37,230 --> 00:03:39,850
You must be joking, professor!
The deadline is too soon!

34
00:03:39,930 --> 00:03:41,100
Quiet, quiet, quiet.

35
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:44,740
I know this is difficult for everyone.

36
00:03:44,820 --> 00:03:49,280
For this assignment,
you will be assigned as a bedroom unit.

37
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,830
Work together as a group.

38
00:03:51,910 --> 00:03:55,730
The materials and content are not limited.

39
00:03:55,810 --> 00:03:58,440
Professionalism is not required.

40
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:01,920
What is important...

41
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,310
is to show everyone's ability
to conceive and imagine.

42
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:11,600
We are good in bedroom designs,
Xiao Tiantian.

43
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:15,560
We're good enough,
but we must endure until the end.

44
00:04:15,640 --> 00:04:19,030
-Why do you care so much?
-It's him.

45
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:22,020
-Gao Ting.
-Classmate Gao Ting.

46
00:04:22,100 --> 00:04:24,600
Gao Ting, wait a minute.

47
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:28,070
I haven't had time to introduce myself.
I am Hu Jing.

48
00:04:28,150 --> 00:04:29,950
You can also call me Fat Tiger.

49
00:04:30,030 --> 00:04:33,070
My name is Hao Tian, so sweet.

50
00:04:33,150 --> 00:04:35,150
Hello, but I don't live in here.

51
00:04:35,230 --> 00:04:37,270
Well, I know.

52
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:39,280
Your dorm bed is always empty.

53
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:41,770
Yes, yes, yes, we just want to ask.

54
00:04:41,850 --> 00:04:45,100
What are you going to do
about the group assignment?

55
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:47,030
-Group assignment?
-Correct.

56
00:04:47,110 --> 00:04:50,770
Professor Gu said
to use the bedroom as a unit.

57
00:04:50,850 --> 00:04:52,080
There should be someone else
in our bedroom, right?

58
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,169
Yes.

59
00:04:53,249 --> 00:04:56,360
Is he willing to cooperate?

60
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,050
-Nan Xi, that...
-Do you need anything?

61
00:05:00,130 --> 00:05:05,010
-I-I-I want to ask you.
-Sorry.

62
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,090
Did you wait for a long time?

63
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:11,470
No. Did class go well today?

64
00:05:11,550 --> 00:05:14,240
-Yes.
-That's great.

65
00:05:16,510 --> 00:05:18,880
So sneaky. What are you doing?

66
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:22,350
Swordswoman,
we have a few words to tell Nan Xi.

67
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:23,930
Speak.

68
00:05:24,010 --> 00:05:25,520
Nan Xi, we think...

69
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:28,000
putting few small dumplings
that meet each other...

70
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,670
in the same steamer...

71
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:32,650
and go through the cultivation of steam
and high temperature...

72
00:05:32,730 --> 00:05:34,380
will make them perfect together.

73
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:36,180
This... What a fate it is, right?

74
00:05:36,260 --> 00:05:38,450
I think this fate is worth cherishing.

75
00:05:38,530 --> 00:05:40,950
I don't like xiao long bao.

76
00:05:45,010 --> 00:05:46,980
I lost to you in the entrance examination.

77
00:05:47,060 --> 00:05:50,950
I hope this time,
we will do our best and compete again.

78
00:05:51,030 --> 00:05:53,060
I'm looking forward to your work.

79
00:05:58,930 --> 00:06:02,430
This... This is just your 0.5 version.

80
00:06:02,510 --> 00:06:05,050
I can tell that both of you
are from the same department.

81
00:06:05,130 --> 00:06:06,650
I am different from him.

82
00:06:06,730 --> 00:06:09,890
Okay, it's just a metaphor.

83
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:13,050
Yes, yes,
our dumplings are also a metaphor.

84
00:06:13,130 --> 00:06:16,000
Actually, today
we just wanted to apologize...

85
00:06:16,080 --> 00:06:18,340
for what happened
on the first day school.

86
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:22,140
Nan Xi, just look at our fate.
We're in the same dormitory.

87
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:25,550
-Forgive us.
-Yes, forgive us.

88
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:27,850
You both already apologized.

89
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:31,150
-Then, do you forgive us?
-Yes.

90
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:32,960
That's great!

91
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:36,930
Swordswoman,
we would like to say sorry to you, too.

92
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:39,930
-Okay.
-Forget it.

93
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,220
Nan Xi, when are you going back
to the dorm?

94
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:44,410
Let's make a model together.

95
00:06:44,490 --> 00:06:47,450
-A model what?
-It's nothing.

96
00:06:47,530 --> 00:06:50,561
-What "dormitory as unit?"
-Don't worry.

97
00:06:50,641 --> 00:06:52,701
-What?
-Nothing.

98
00:06:58,410 --> 00:07:02,910
-Am I doing this right?
-It's like this.

99
00:07:04,530 --> 00:07:06,330
The two of them are here.

100
00:07:07,550 --> 00:07:13,070
-Coming... Coming...
-Come, come in.

101
00:07:13,150 --> 00:07:15,410
-Hello.
-Why do you look like that?

102
00:07:15,490 --> 00:07:17,450
Come in fast, come in.

103
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:24,700
So unique.

104
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:28,840
Artistic.

105
00:07:30,250 --> 00:07:34,880
Sure enough, the aesthetic of God Nan Xi
cannot be understood by us mortals.

106
00:07:34,960 --> 00:07:38,170
Nan Xi, what is this for?

107
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:41,280
Do you want to camp indoors?

108
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:45,040
Yes, don't most rented houses come
with their own furniture?

109
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,880
Why is there nothing here?

110
00:07:46,960 --> 00:07:48,470
How do you live?

111
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:54,030
Nan Xi likes the house without anything,
so it's easy to renovate.

112
00:07:54,110 --> 00:07:57,400
Come here, Cheng Erluo, come here.

113
00:08:01,340 --> 00:08:03,870
It's quite pretty. Go, paint the wall.

114
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:08,290
Did you ask me over
just to be your painter?

115
00:08:08,370 --> 00:08:10,990
It's easy. Wait for the furniture
to be added later.

116
00:08:11,070 --> 00:08:12,750
That's real physical work.

117
00:08:12,830 --> 00:08:14,750
I thought I was here to clean up.

118
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:16,150
You're asking me to do such a thing.

119
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:17,540
It's okay. I'll help you with it.

120
00:08:17,620 --> 00:08:19,310
That won't work.

121
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:22,950
Come here.
Rest and watch us do physical work.

122
00:08:23,030 --> 00:08:24,460
Hurry up. What are you doing?

123
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:26,360
Good.

124
00:10:57,330 --> 00:11:02,050
Xia Rui, these are some of the works
that Nan Xi left at home that I packed.

125
00:11:02,130 --> 00:11:04,250
I don't know if it's what Nan Xi prefers.

126
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:06,650
Contact me if you need more.

127
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:10,130
With these, it will look like a home.

128
00:11:11,530 --> 00:11:12,830
One.

129
00:11:18,830 --> 00:11:20,130
Two.

130
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,350
Three.

131
00:11:23,130 --> 00:11:24,850
Xia Rui, I'm back.

132
00:11:24,930 --> 00:11:28,230
Look, I have prepared a little surprise
for you.

133
00:11:33,730 --> 00:11:35,750
Auntie sent them here for you.

134
00:11:35,830 --> 00:11:37,250
What's wrong?

135
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:40,130
These are not right.

136
00:11:50,930 --> 00:11:52,250
What are you doing?

137
00:11:52,330 --> 00:11:54,450
Didn't you say you didn't want them?

138
00:11:54,530 --> 00:11:55,850
Didn't you say you don't like them?

139
00:11:55,930 --> 00:11:59,130
I will put them away and send them back.

140
00:12:00,630 --> 00:12:04,250
Anyway, you think these things
are superfluous.

141
00:12:04,330 --> 00:12:06,530
I didn't mean that.

142
00:12:07,530 --> 00:12:09,950
I just want you to feel...

143
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:12,450
that you can adapt better
if you had your belongings.

144
00:12:12,530 --> 00:12:15,150
I just wanted you to feel at home.

145
00:12:15,230 --> 00:12:19,350
I'm sorry for being superfluous.

146
00:12:19,430 --> 00:12:21,250
Who said you were superfluous?

147
00:12:21,330 --> 00:12:22,850
You said it.

148
00:12:22,930 --> 00:12:25,730
You said you didn't like it just now.

149
00:12:28,730 --> 00:12:30,430
I like it.

150
00:12:32,330 --> 00:12:34,550
You're so inconsistent.

151
00:12:34,630 --> 00:12:37,330
Let you talk about the good and the bad.

152
00:12:40,930 --> 00:12:44,550
I mean, I like everything you do.

153
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:48,050
It's just...
These things, they're not right.

154
00:12:48,130 --> 00:12:50,450
Didn't you do all those things?

155
00:12:50,530 --> 00:12:52,250
How are they not right?

156
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:54,950
Many of these are semi-finished
and experimental products...

157
00:12:55,030 --> 00:12:57,250
which cannot be displayed.

158
00:12:57,330 --> 00:13:00,330
You call those semi-finished products?

159
00:13:01,930 --> 00:13:06,250
I think these semi-finished products
will definitely be sold at a good price.

160
00:13:06,330 --> 00:13:09,050
What a pity.
If you don't like it, I will pack it.

161
00:13:09,130 --> 00:13:11,130
Don't pack this.

162
00:13:13,230 --> 00:13:15,250
I didn't get to buy flowers
this morning...

163
00:13:15,330 --> 00:13:18,250
so I just threw in two celery
to see the effect.

164
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:20,850
Keep this, I like it.

165
00:13:20,930 --> 00:13:23,800
Strange,
there are so many beautiful pieces,

166
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:25,850
yet you call them semi-finished products.

167
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:29,150
I put a few celery in here,
and you say it is a piece of art.

168
00:13:29,230 --> 00:13:31,650
I really don't understand
your elite aesthetics.

169
00:13:31,730 --> 00:13:33,950
Fine. I'll give it to you if you like it.

170
00:13:34,030 --> 00:13:37,250
I made many things in this house.

171
00:13:37,330 --> 00:13:39,450
This is the only one you made.

172
00:13:39,530 --> 00:13:43,050
Celery flower arrangements...
They're just right.

173
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:46,530
I like everything you do.

174
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:49,050
Don't flatter me.

175
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:50,550
I don't know how to make any furniture.

176
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:52,350
What will you let me do? What can I do?

177
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:54,050
Flower arrangements.

178
00:13:54,130 --> 00:13:57,450
Look, the green pairs up with the yellow.

179
00:13:57,530 --> 00:13:59,730
Doesn't it look like an art piece?

180
00:14:00,830 --> 00:14:03,450
Just a few celeries make an art piece?

181
00:14:03,530 --> 00:14:05,450
You're such a bootlicker.

182
00:14:05,530 --> 00:14:09,230
But I quite like it.

183
00:14:10,730 --> 00:14:13,250
Okay, let's go buy flowers tomorrow.

184
00:14:13,330 --> 00:14:15,050
I'll help you buy fresh flowers everyday.

185
00:14:15,130 --> 00:14:16,750
Okay.

186
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:22,350
As for this, let's settle it tonight.

187
00:14:22,430 --> 00:14:24,530
How do you want it to die?

188
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:28,050
Fried beef or fried pork,

189
00:14:28,130 --> 00:14:31,730
sliced or diced?

190
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:36,440
All of those are fine. You decide.

191
00:14:49,130 --> 00:14:50,050
Nan Xi, look.

192
00:14:50,130 --> 00:14:52,730
Nan Xi, Nan Xi, look.

193
00:15:02,830 --> 00:15:05,530
Why are you exercising?

194
00:15:06,930 --> 00:15:07,850
Are you back?

195
00:15:07,930 --> 00:15:09,250
Yes.

196
00:15:09,330 --> 00:15:12,250
Xia Rui, you are back.

197
00:15:12,330 --> 00:15:15,150
You're starving us to death.

198
00:15:15,230 --> 00:15:19,050
Can I starve you? I am not that capable.

199
00:15:19,130 --> 00:15:21,050
You are lazy.

200
00:15:21,130 --> 00:15:22,850
There are so many snacks.

201
00:15:22,930 --> 00:15:25,050
Starving you is a small issue.

202
00:15:25,130 --> 00:15:27,850
-What should we do if Nan Xi starves?
-Be careful, I'll beat you up.

203
00:15:27,930 --> 00:15:32,050
Isn't it unhygienic to order in?

204
00:15:32,130 --> 00:15:36,050
By the way, is your ready-made kitchen
still unused?

205
00:15:36,130 --> 00:15:38,950
How about we do it at our house tonight?

206
00:15:39,030 --> 00:15:41,950
I called Shu over.
She'll come after her rehearsal.

207
00:15:42,030 --> 00:15:43,750
Who said that our kitchen
has not been used?

208
00:15:43,830 --> 00:15:45,450
What?

209
00:15:45,530 --> 00:15:49,450
The two of you secretly used the stove
behind my back?

210
00:15:49,530 --> 00:15:52,050
Don't eat snacks, let me cook.

211
00:15:52,130 --> 00:15:56,050
What? Can Nan Xi cook by himself?

212
00:15:56,130 --> 00:15:58,650
I must have my meal here tonight.

213
00:15:58,730 --> 00:16:01,250
Otherwise, you both are partnering
to sideline me.

214
00:16:01,330 --> 00:16:03,650
This isn't the first time.
Did you just realize that?

215
00:16:03,730 --> 00:16:06,850
No, Xia Rui, you will lose me easily.

216
00:16:06,930 --> 00:16:09,250
All right, all right, just one meal.

217
00:16:09,330 --> 00:16:10,650
Didn't you want to call Shu over?

218
00:16:10,730 --> 00:16:12,650
It's been long since we gathered.
Stay for a meal here.

219
00:16:12,730 --> 00:16:15,050
Let Nan Xi cook, okay?

220
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:16,250
Okay.

221
00:16:16,330 --> 00:16:17,200
That'll be it.

222
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:19,930
You came up with this idea.
You go grocery shopping.

223
00:16:21,130 --> 00:16:22,400
Fine, I will buy them.

224
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:25,450
I'm errand boy material.
I acknowledge that.

225
00:16:25,530 --> 00:16:27,330
What should I buy? Tell me.

226
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:29,750
-Striped bass...
-Pork belly.

227
00:16:29,830 --> 00:16:31,330
What?

228
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:33,250
-Chili.
-Tomato.

229
00:16:33,330 --> 00:16:36,850
Wait, wait, wait. Decide on one.

230
00:16:36,930 --> 00:16:38,550
-Scrambled eggs with green onion.
-Broccoli sirloin.

231
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:40,450
No. What do you actually want?

232
00:16:40,530 --> 00:16:43,850
Add on some cola and chicken wings.

233
00:16:43,930 --> 00:16:45,330
What?

234
00:16:47,430 --> 00:16:49,730
-Just buy them.
-Just buy them.

235
00:16:59,130 --> 00:17:02,930
Didn't you say you were cooking at home?
Why did it change to pizza?

236
00:17:04,030 --> 00:17:06,150
Wouldn't it be good
if you were like this earlier?

237
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,730
Next time, will you still dare to ask?

238
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:11,450
I don't care.

239
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,550
Nan Xi's cooking,
I will try it sooner or later.

240
00:17:13,630 --> 00:17:15,730
I will not give up.

241
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:24,350
What are you doing, Shu?

242
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,050
Why are there so many lemons?

243
00:17:26,130 --> 00:17:27,550
I'm making lemonade.

244
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:30,550
The human body needs 100 milligrams
of vitamin C everyday.

245
00:17:30,630 --> 00:17:31,850
I need five-and-a-half lemons.

246
00:17:31,930 --> 00:17:34,850
These are not even enough for us.

247
00:17:34,930 --> 00:17:37,250
Just drink C100.

248
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:40,530
Sweet and sour.
It's definitely better than lemonade.

249
00:17:41,630 --> 00:17:44,750
Remember to come
and help me after finishing this.

250
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,450
Hmm, it's better than lemonade.

251
00:17:46,530 --> 00:17:47,650
Come on.

252
00:17:47,730 --> 00:17:49,550
Coming.

253
00:17:49,630 --> 00:17:51,450
How is it? How is it?

254
00:17:51,530 --> 00:17:54,050
A little bit higher on the right.

255
00:17:54,130 --> 00:17:55,950
A little bit higher?

256
00:17:56,030 --> 00:17:58,850
Yes, yes, lower it a little bit.

257
00:17:58,930 --> 00:18:00,250
All right, all right. It's good.

258
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:01,350
I will be nailing it.

259
00:18:01,430 --> 00:18:03,050
Okay, watch out for your hand.

260
